data.title: The Best Songs Produced By DJ Mustard, Ranked by Fans
data.meta_description: Explore this curated list of the best songs produced by DJ Mustard, including Rack City, Needed Me, and more - ranked by fans.
data.text:
DJ Mustard (also known as Mustard) has carved out a prominent space in the music industry with his signature sound - a fusion of West Coast vibes and catchy hooks that make you want to hit the dance floor immediately. His production skills are second to none, characterized by infectious melodies, hard-hitting drums, and an innate ability to create beats that stay with you long after the track ends.

A standout song produced by DJ Mustard is "Rack City" by Tyga. This explosive collaboration catapulted both artists into mainstream success and showcased DJ Mustard's unrivaled skill for crafting unforgettable anthems. With its infectious synth riff and heavy bassline, this track has become a staple at parties worldwide, igniting crowds every time it drops. However, don't forget about the huge success that was "I Don't F*ck with You" by Big Sean featuring E-40. This anthem became an instant hit thanks to its irresistible bounce and clap-along beat. It perfectly showcases how he can take simple elements and transform them into multi-platinum magic.

What sets DJ Mustard apart from other producers is his innate ability to collaborate with some of the biggest names in the industry. From pop sensations like Rihanna, to rap icons like Kendrick Lamar (yes, he helped produce a song included in the Drake/Kendrick battle of 2024) and 2 Chainz, DJ Mustard's versatility shines through in every collaboration. He elevates each artist's sound while still maintaining his unique touch, resulting in chart-topping hits that take the world by storm.

So, get ready to add these tunes to your playlist because once you experience the magic of DJ Mustard's productions, there's no turning back.
